{"title_page": "Alain Chuard", "text_new": "{{Infobox person\n| name = Alain Chuard\n| image = Alain Chuard.jpg\n| image_size=190\n| caption = \n| birth_name = Alain Marc Chuard\n| birth_date = \n| birth_place = [[Bern]], [[Switzerland]]\n| nationality = Swiss\n| residence = [[Palo Alto]], [[California]], [[United States|US]]\n| alma_mater = [[Macalester College]] <br/> [[Stanford Graduate School of Business]]\n| occupation = Entrepreneur <br/> Former professional snowboarder\n| spouse = {{marriage|[[Victoria Ransom]]|2013}}\n| children = 3 \n| website = {{URL|http://www.alainchuard.com/}}\n}}\n\n'''Alain Chuard''' is a Swiss serial entrepreneur and former professional snowboarder living in [[Palo Alto, California]].<ref name=tages>{{cite web |url=http://www.tagesanzeiger.ch/wirtschaft/unternehmen-und-konjunktur/Der-wichtigste-Wendepunkt-war-dass-ich-mit-Snowboarden-begann/story/16693807 |title=Der wichtigste Wendepunkt war, dass ich mit Snowboarden begann |author=Mathias Morgenthaler|date=June 6, 2014 |publisher=Tages-Anzeiger |access-date=October 9, 2015}}</ref><ref name=berner>{{cite web |url=http://www.bernerzeitung.ch/wirtschaft/unternehmen-und-konjunktur/Berner-verkauft-sein-Unternehmen-fuer-250-Millionen-an-Google/story/12665662 |title=Berner verkauft sein Unternehmen f\u00fcr 250 Millionen an Google |author=Jon Mettler |date=August 8, 2012 |publisher=Bernerzeitung |access-date=October 9, 2015}}</ref><ref name=pleasure>{{cite web |url=http://www.pleasuremag.com/plsr115-die-karriere-danach |title=Smartshitting For Smart People: Die Karriere Danach |author=Christian  \u00d6fner |date=June 15, 2015 |publisher=Pleasure Verlags GmbH & Co. KG |access-date=October 9, 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150618000058/http://www.pleasuremag.com/plsr115-die-karriere-danach |archive-date=June 18, 2015 |url-status=dead |df=mdy-all }}</ref> He is best known as the founder and [[Chief product officer]] of [[Wildfire Interactive]], the social media marketing technology company acquired by [[Google]] in July 2012.<ref name=tages/>\n\n==Early life and education==\nChuard was born in [[Bern]] and raised in the Swiss town of [[Bolligen]].<ref name=berner/><ref name=startup/> His father and uncle were both entrepreneurs.<ref name=handels/><ref name=min/>\n\nChuard competed on the snowboard World-Cup Pro Tour while in high school.<ref name=aspen1/> From 1994-96, he was ranked in the top 4 snowboarders in Switzerland.<ref name=berner/> Chuard was sponsored by [[Burton Snowboards]] and has been featured in various snowboarding publications including the cover of ''[[Transworld Snowboarding]]''.<ref name=pleasure/><ref name=handels/><ref name=snowboarding>{{cite web |url=http://snowboarding.transworld.net/photos/the-tws-100-photo-list-every-rider-who-made-the-mag/#CkdwvxYZCc7Srd70.97 |title=The TWS 100 Photo List: Every Rider Who Made The Mag |date=October 31, 2001 |publisher= The Enthusiast Network |access-date=October 9, 2015}}</ref>\n\nChuard left Switzerland at the age of 20 after completing his high school [[matura]].<ref name=min>{{cite web |url=http://www.20min.ch/finance/news/story/Ein-Schweizer-erobert-das-Silicon-Valley-30742107 |title=Ein Schweizer erobert das Silicon Valley |author=Manuel B\u00fchlmann |date=August 7, 2012 |access-date=October 9, 2015}}</ref> Chuard studied [[mathematics]] and [[economics]] at [[Macalester College]].<ref name=handels>{{cite web |url=http://www.handelszeitung.ch/unternehmen/350-millionen-google-verpasst-schweizer-den-ritterschlag |title=350 Millionen: Google verpasst Schweizer den Ritterschlag |author=Nele Husmann |date=August 20, 2012 |publisher=AXEL SPRINGER SCHWEIZ AG |access-date=October 9, 2015}}</ref><ref name=entre>{{cite web |url=http://www.entrepreneur.com/article/219911 |title=The Spark That Fuels Wildfire Interactive |author=John Shinal |date=June 28, 2011 |publisher=Entrepreneur Media Inc |access-date=October 9, 2015}}</ref> He has an [[Master of Business Administration|MBA]] from the [[Stanford Graduate School of Business]].<ref name=berner/>\n\n==Career==\nAfter graduating from [[Macalester College]], he spent two years working as a financial analyst for [[Salomon Smith Barney]] in [[New York City]].<ref name=berner/> He then left Wall Street to start the adventure travel company, Access Trips, in 2001.<ref name=min/> While getting his MBA, he also built an online booking and CRM software called IncFuel Corp.<ref name=aspen1>{{cite web|url=http://agln.aspeninstitute.org/fellows/alain-chuard |title=Fellow Profile: Alain Chuard |publisher=The Aspen Institute |access-date=October 9, 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160306023901/http://agln.aspeninstitute.org/fellows/alain-chuard |archivedate=March 6, 2016 }}</ref> In the summer of 2007, he was an [[Entrepreneur in Residence]] at [[Highland Capital Partners]] in [[Boston]].<ref name=bloomberg>{{cite web |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/bw/articles/2012-10-04/running-a-startup-incubator-for-fun-not-profit |title=Running a Startup Incubator for Fun, Not Profit |author=Mark Milian |date=October 4, 2012 |publisher=Bloomberg LP |access-date=October 9, 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn 2008, Chuard developed the software Promotion Builder as an online marketing tool used for promoting Access Trips through social media.<ref name=handels/><ref name=entre/> Promotion Builder became Wildfire Interactive and within four years, Wildfire grew to a company with 400 employees.<ref name=srf>{{cite web |url=http://www.srf.ch/news/wirtschaft/swiss-economic-forum-2014/alain-chuard-der-berner-google-millionaer-2 |title=Alain Chuard, der Berner Google-Million\u00e4r |last1=Siegert |first1=Manuela |last2=Brennwald |first2=Reto |date=May 29, 2014|publisher=SRF Schweizer Radio und Fernsehen |access-date=October 9, 2015}}</ref>  In 2010, Chuard sold Access Trips in order to focus on Wildfire.<ref name=startup>{{cite web |url=http://www.startupticker.ch/en/news/june-2014/how-to-sell-your-company-to-google-or-twitter |title=How to sell your company to Google or Twitter |date=June 6, 2014 |publisher=startupticker.ch |access-date=October 9, 2015}}</ref><ref name=handels/><ref name=entre/> In July 2012, Google purchased Wildfire for a reported $450 million.<ref name=tages/><ref name=tech>{{cite web |url=https://techcrunch.com/2012/08/06/google-wildfire-100-million/ |title=Google Slaps $100M Golden Handcuffs On Wildfire To Retain Employees After $350M Acquisition |author=Josh Constine |date=August 6, 2012 |publisher=TechCrunch |access-date=October 9, 2015}}</ref> Since 2014, he leads the Google My Business division.<ref name=aspen1/> He is a Henry Crown Fellow of the [[Aspen Institute]].<ref name=aspen2>{{cite web |url=http://www.aspeninstitute.org/leadership-programs/henry-crown-fellowship-program/lists-fellows/2015-class |title=The Aspen Institute Announces the 2015 Class of Henry Crown Fellows |publisher=Aspen Institute |access-date=October 9, 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nChuard married [[Victoria Ransom]] in March 2013.<ref name=handels/> They met in December 1999 while studying at Macalester College.<ref name=min/> He speaks four languages and is one of the 300 wealthiest people in Switzerland.<ref name=entre/><ref name=srf/>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Chuard, Alain}}\n[[Category:Google employees]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Macalester College alumni]]\n[[Category:Stanford Graduate School of Business alumni]]\n[[Category:Swiss businesspeople]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:People from Bern]]\n[[Category:Henry Crown Fellows]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox person\n| name = Alain Chuard\n| image = Alain Chuard.jpg\n| image_size=190\n| caption = \n| birth_name = Alain Marc Chuard\n| birth_date = \n| birth_place = [[Bern]], [[Switzerland]]\n| nationality = Swiss\n| residence = [[Palo Alto]], [[California]], [[United States|US]]\n| alma_mater = [[Macalester College]] <br/> [[Stanford Graduate School of Business]]\n| occupation = Entrepreneur <br/> Former professional snowboarder\n| spouse = {{marriage|[[Victoria Ransom]]|2013}}\n| children = 3 \n| website = {{URL|http://www.alainchuard.com/}}\n}}\n\n'''Alain Chuard''' is a Swiss serial entrepreneur and former professional snowboarder living in [[Palo Alto, California]].<ref name=tages>{{cite web |url=http://www.tagesanzeiger.ch/wirtschaft/unternehmen-und-konjunktur/Der-wichtigste-Wendepunkt-war-dass-ich-mit-Snowboarden-begann/story/16693807 |title=Der wichtigste Wendepunkt war, dass ich mit Snowboarden begann |author=Mathias Morgenthaler|date=June 6, 2014 |publisher=Tages-Anzeiger |access-date=October 9, 2015}}</ref><ref name=berner>{{cite web |url=http://www.bernerzeitung.ch/wirtschaft/unternehmen-und-konjunktur/Berner-verkauft-sein-Unternehmen-fuer-250-Millionen-an-Google/story/12665662 |title=Berner verkauft sein Unternehmen f\u00fcr 250 Millionen an Google |author=Jon Mettler |date=August 8, 2012 |publisher=Bernerzeitung |access-date=October 9, 2015}}</ref><ref name=pleasure>{{cite web |url=http://www.pleasuremag.com/plsr115-die-karriere-danach |title=Smartshitting For Smart People: Die Karriere Danach |author=Christian  \u00d6fner |date=June 15, 2015 |publisher=Pleasure Verlags GmbH & Co. KG |access-date=October 9, 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150618000058/http://www.pleasuremag.com/plsr115-die-karriere-danach |archive-date=June 18, 2015 |url-status=dead |df=mdy-all }}</ref> He is best known as the founder and [[Chief product officer]] of [[Wildfire Interactive]], the social media marketing technology company acquired by [[Google]] in July 2012.<ref name=tages/>\n\n==Early life and education==\nChuard was born in [[Bern]] and raised in the Swiss town of [[Bolligen]].<ref name=berner/><ref name=startup/> His father and uncle were both entrepreneurs.<ref name=handels/><ref name=min/>\n\nChuard competed on the snowboard World-Cup Pro Tour while in high school.<ref name=aspen1/> From 1994-96, he was ranked in the top 4 snowboarders in Switzerland.<ref name=berner/> Chuard was sponsored by [[Burton Snowboards]] and has been featured in various snowboarding publications including the cover of ''[[Transworld Snowboarding]]''.<ref name=pleasure/><ref name=handels/><ref name=snowboarding>{{cite web |url=http://snowboarding.transworld.net/photos/the-tws-100-photo-list-every-rider-who-made-the-mag/#CkdwvxYZCc7Srd70.97 |title=The TWS 100 Photo List: Every Rider Who Made The Mag |date=October 31, 2001 |publisher= The Enthusiast Network |access-date=October 9, 2015}}</ref>\n\nChuard left Switzerland at the age of 20 after completing his high school [[matura]].<ref name=min>{{cite web |url=http://www.20min.ch/finance/news/story/Ein-Schweizer-erobert-das-Silicon-Valley-30742107 |title=Ein Schweizer erobert das Silicon Valley |author=Manuel B\u00fchlmann |date=August 7, 2012 |access-date=October 9, 2015}}</ref> Chuard studied [[mathematics]] and [[economics]] at [[Macalester College]].<ref name=handels>{{cite web |url=http://www.handelszeitung.ch/unternehmen/350-millionen-google-verpasst-schweizer-den-ritterschlag |title=350 Millionen: Google verpasst Schweizer den Ritterschlag |author=Nele Husmann |date=August 20, 2012 |publisher=AXEL SPRINGER SCHWEIZ AG |access-date=October 9, 2015}}</ref><ref name=entre>{{cite web |url=http://www.entrepreneur.com/article/219911 |title=The Spark That Fuels Wildfire Interactive |author=John Shinal |date=June 28, 2011 |publisher=Entrepreneur Media Inc |access-date=October 9, 2015}}</ref> He has an [[Masters of Business Administration|MBA]] from the [[Stanford Graduate School of Business]].<ref name=berner/>\n\n==Career==\nAfter graduating from [[Macalester College]], he spent two years working as a financial analyst for [[Salomon Smith Barney]] in [[New York City]].<ref name=berner/> He then left Wall Street to start the adventure travel company, Access Trips, in 2001.<ref name=min/> While getting his MBA, he also built an online booking and CRM software called IncFuel Corp.<ref name=aspen1>{{cite web|url=http://agln.aspeninstitute.org/fellows/alain-chuard |title=Fellow Profile: Alain Chuard |publisher=The Aspen Institute |access-date=October 9, 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160306023901/http://agln.aspeninstitute.org/fellows/alain-chuard |archivedate=March 6, 2016 }}</ref> In the summer of 2007, he was an [[Entrepreneur in Residence]] at [[Highland Capital Partners]] in [[Boston]].<ref name=bloomberg>{{cite web |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/bw/articles/2012-10-04/running-a-startup-incubator-for-fun-not-profit |title=Running a Startup Incubator for Fun, Not Profit |author=Mark Milian |date=October 4, 2012 |publisher=Bloomberg LP |access-date=October 9, 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn 2008, Chuard developed the software Promotion Builder as an online marketing tool used for promoting Access Trips through social media.<ref name=handels/><ref name=entre/> Promotion Builder became Wildfire Interactive and within four years, Wildfire grew to a company with 400 employees.<ref name=srf>{{cite web |url=http://www.srf.ch/news/wirtschaft/swiss-economic-forum-2014/alain-chuard-der-berner-google-millionaer-2 |title=Alain Chuard, der Berner Google-Million\u00e4r |last1=Siegert |first1=Manuela |last2=Brennwald |first2=Reto |date=May 29, 2014|publisher=SRF Schweizer Radio und Fernsehen |access-date=October 9, 2015}}</ref>  In 2010, Chuard sold Access Trips in order to focus on Wildfire.<ref name=startup>{{cite web |url=http://www.startupticker.ch/en/news/june-2014/how-to-sell-your-company-to-google-or-twitter |title=How to sell your company to Google or Twitter |date=June 6, 2014 |publisher=startupticker.ch |access-date=October 9, 2015}}</ref><ref name=handels/><ref name=entre/> In July 2012, Google purchased Wildfire for a reported $450 million.<ref name=tages/><ref name=tech>{{cite web |url=https://techcrunch.com/2012/08/06/google-wildfire-100-million/ |title=Google Slaps $100M Golden Handcuffs On Wildfire To Retain Employees After $350M Acquisition |author=Josh Constine |date=August 6, 2012 |publisher=TechCrunch |access-date=October 9, 2015}}</ref> Since 2014, he leads the Google My Business division.<ref name=aspen1/> He is a Henry Crown Fellow of the [[Aspen Institute]].<ref name=aspen2>{{cite web |url=http://www.aspeninstitute.org/leadership-programs/henry-crown-fellowship-program/lists-fellows/2015-class |title=The Aspen Institute Announces the 2015 Class of Henry Crown Fellows |publisher=Aspen Institute |access-date=October 9, 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nChuard married [[Victoria Ransom]] in March 2013.<ref name=handels/> They met in December 1999 while studying at Macalester College.<ref name=min/> He speaks four languages and is one of the 300 wealthiest people in Switzerland.<ref name=entre/><ref name=srf/>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Chuard, Alain}}\n[[Category:Google employees]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Macalester College alumni]]\n[[Category:Stanford Graduate School of Business alumni]]\n[[Category:Swiss businesspeople]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:People from Bern]]\n[[Category:Henry Crown Fellows]]\n", "name_user": "EdmundT", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eEarly life and education:Spelling", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alain_Chuard"}
