riginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|17|df=yes}}\n| Aux1            = {{USD|97000|long=no}}\n| ShortSummary    = \n| LineColor       = 7FF10D\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 3\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 3\n| Title           = Revenge Is a Dish Best Served Hot\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|17|df=yes}}\n| Aux1            = {{USD|94000|long=no}}\n| ShortSummary    = \n| LineColor       = 7FF10D\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 4\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 4\n| Title           = Two's Company, Three's a ... Threesome\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|17|df=yes}}\n| Aux1            = {{USD|94000|long=no}}\n| ShortSummary    = \n| LineColor       = 7FF10D\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 5\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 5\n| Title           = Boys to Men\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|17|df=yes}}\n| Aux1            = {{USD|75000|long=no}}\n| ShortSummary    = \n| LineColor       = 7FF10D\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 6\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 6\n| Title           = The Bryce Isn't Right\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|17|df=yes}}\n| Aux1            = {{USD|55000|long=no}}\n| ShortSummary    = \n| LineColor       = 7FF10D\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 7\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 7\n| Title           = Sisters over Misters\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|17|df=yes}}\n| Aux1            = {{USD|43000|long=no}}\n| ShortSummary    = \n| LineColor       = 7FF10D\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 8\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 8\n| Title           = Lust or Bust\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|17|df=yes}}\n| Aux1            = {{USD|75000|long=no}}\n| ShortSummary    = \n| LineColor       = 7FF10D\n}}\n}}\n\n== Production ==\n=== Background ===\nThe show was created by Laura Gibson and developed by Charlie Bennett, citing ''[[Seinfeld]]'' episode, \"[[The Contest (Seinfeld episode)|The Contest]]\" as their inspiration for the premise of ''Too Hot to Handle''.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Kurkland |first1=Daniel |title=Too Hot To Handle: Awesome Facts About The Making Of Netflix's New Show |url=https://www.thethings.com/too-hot-to-handle-netflix-show-facts-making-of/ |website=TheThings.com |accessdate=19 April 2020 |date=17 April 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref> Laura Gibson, creative director of [[Fremantle (company)|Fremantle]]-owned production company [[Talkback (production company)|Talkback]], which produced the eight-part series, told ''[[Deadline (magazine)|Deadline]]'' that she had been working to produce a dating show since 2016.<ref name=\"inspiration\">{{cite web |last1=White |first1=Peter |title=\u2018Too Hot To Handle\u2019: Producers Dish The Dirt On Netflix Reality Show That Combines \u2018Seinfeld\u2019s \u2018The Contest\u2019 With \u2018Love Island\u2019 |url=https://deadline.com/2020/04/too-hot-to-handle-love-island-seinfeld-the-contest-netflix-1202910204/ |website=deadline.com |publisher=Deadline |accessdate=19 April 2020 |date=16 April 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nViki Kolar and Jonno Richards, executive producers for ''Too Hot to Handle'', said they found inspiration for the virtual character from [[artificial intelligence]] and [[Virtual assistant|virtual assistants]], especially in [[Artificial intelligence for video surveillance|video surveillance]]. Viki Kolar stated, \"[A.I.] is literally everywhere around us. It's kind of governing us, it's taking over,\" in an interview with ''[[Glamour (magazine)|Glamour]]''.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Tannenbaum |first1=Emily |title=Netflix\u2019s Too Hot to Handle Is the Funniest, Least Sexy Reality Show About Sex |url=https://www.glamour.com/story/netflix-too-hot-to-handle-review |website=glamour.com |publisher=Glamour |accessdate=19 April 2020 |date=17 April 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n=== Development ===\nOn 5 May 2019, [[Netflix|Netflix Studios, LLC]] applied to trademark the phrase \"Too Hot to Handle\" for all educational, training, entertainment, sporting, and cultural purposes. The application was approved on 24 June 2019, and was extended on 5 March 2020.<ref name=\"trademark\">{{cite web |title=TOO HOT TO HANDLE - Trademark Details |url=https://trademarks.justia.com/884/51/too-hot-to-88451346.html |website=trademarks.justia.com |publisher=Justia Trademarks |accessdate=27 March 2020 |date=29 May 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> This has been done with other [[List of original programs distributed by Netflix|Netflix original programs]] such as ''[[Stranger Things]]'', ''[[The OA]]'', and ''[[Big Mouth (TV series)|Big Mouth]]''.<ref>{{cite web |title=Netflix Studios, LLC Trademarks |url=https://trademarks.justia.com/owners/netflix-studios-llc-3160899/ |website=trademarks.justia.com |publisher=Justia Trademarks |accessdate=27 March 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref> ''Too Hot to Handle'' was produced by [[Fremantle (company)|Fremantle]] production company [[Talkback (production company)|Talkback]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=White |first1=Peter |title='Too Hot To Handle': Netflix Unveils Trailer & Sets Premiere For Steamy Reality Dating Format |url=https://deadline.com/video/too-hot-to-handle-netflix-premiere-trailer/ |website=deadline.com |publisher=Deadline |accessdate=10 April 2020 |date=10 April 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe show, instead of using a human as their host, used a [[virtual assistant]] named Lana. [[Desiree Burch]] provided voice-over narration, making snarky and comedic remarks towards the contestants.<ref name=\"narrator\">{{cite web |last1=Smail |first1=Gretchen |title='Too Hot To Handle' Narrator Desiree Burch Is The Perfect Person For The Job |url=https://www.bustle.com/p/too-hot-to-handle-narrator-desiree-burch-is-the-perfect-person-for-the-job-22794089 |website=bustle.com |publisher=Bustle |accessdate=17 April 2020 |date=17 April 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n=== Casting ===\nIn 2018, [[Talkback (production company)|Talkback]] announced that casting for an untitled reality television show was open.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Murphy |first1=Desiree |title='Too Hot to Handle' Cast Teases What to Expect From the No-Sex Dating Series (Exclusive) |url=https://www.etonline.com/too-hot-to-handle-cast-teases-what-to-expect-from-the-no-sex-dating-series-exclusive-144771 |website=etonline.com |publisher=Entertainment Tonight |accessdate=20 April 2020 |date=16 April 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref> In total, over 3,000 people auditioned for the show; however, producer Louise Peet stated that the people who ultimately ended up being on the show stood out to the casting team and were chosen quickly.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Nicolaou |first1=Elena |title=The Too Hot to Handle Cast and Creators Answer Your Burning Questions |url=https://www.oprahmag.com/entertainment/a32158960/too-hot-to-handle-netflix-facts-rules/ |website=oprahmag.com |publisher=The Oprah Magazine |accessdate=20 April 2020 |date=18 April 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n=== Filming ===\nA luxury resort called [https://casatau.com/ Casa Tau] in [[Punta Mita]], [[Mexico]] opened to guests in December 2018.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Lague |first1=Adam |title=Is This the Most Luxurious Home in Punta Mita? |url=https://magazine.luxuryretreats.com/casa-tau-most-luxurious-home-punta-mita/ |website=magazine.luxuryretreat.com |publisher=Luxury Retreats Magazine |accessdate=17 April 2020 |date=27 March 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> Soon after, ''Too Hot to Handle'' started filming at Casa Tau in late-March 2019<ref>{{cite web |last1=Brockington |first1=Ariana |title=This Is When All The Too Hot To Handle Action Was Filmed |url=https://www.refinery29.com/en-us/2020/04/9685374/when-was-too-hot-to-handle-filmed-netflix |website=refinery29.com |publisher=Refinery29 |accessdate=19 April 2020 |date=18 April 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref> and ended filming in April.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Blanton |first1=Kayla |title=Where Was 'Too Hot To Handle' Filmed? You Can Plan Your Own Luxury Stay |url=https://www.bustle.com/p/where-was-too-hot-to-handle-filmed-you-can-plan-your-own-luxury-stay-22817237 |website=bustle.com |publisher=Bustle |accessdate=17 April 2020 |date=16 April 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Nicolaou |first1=Elena |title=Netflix's Too Hot to Handle Was Filmed at This $15,660-a-Night Mexican Villa |url=https://www.oprahmag.com/entertainment/tv-movies/a32110085/netflix-too-hot-to-handle-filming-location/ |website=oprahmah.com |publisher=The Oprah Magazine |accessdate=19 April 2020 |date=18 April 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref> After filming had ended, all fourteen contestants were able to spend several days at the resort with no cameras before going home.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Baty |first1=Emma |title=Harry and Francesca From 'Too Hot to Handle' Felt Like the Group Was \"Against\" Them During the Retreat |url=https://www.cosmopolitan.com/entertainment/tv/a32173308/harry-francesca-too-hot-to-handle-interview/ |website=cosmopolitan.com |publisher=Cosmopolitan |accessdate=19 April 2020 |date=17 April 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n=== Release ===\nOn 10 April 2020, [[Netflix]] released the trailer for the first season of ''Too Hot to Handle''.<ref name=\"trailer\">{{cite web |title=Season 1 Trailer: Too Hot to Handle |url=https://www.netflix.com/watch/81189742?trackId=14277282&tctx=0%2C0%2C1a03b184-4d1a-4d08-ae4d-cd1d13d41a6e-4706103%2C%2C |publisher=Netflix |accessdate=10 April 2020 |date=10 April 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref> The first season of ''Too Hot to Handle'' consisted of eight episodes,<ref>{{cite web |last1=Corinthios |first1=Aurelie |title=Netlix Drops Too Hot to Handle Trailer: See 10 Hot Singles Attempt Celibacy for a $100K Prize |url=https://people.com/tv/netflix-too-hot-to-handle-trailer/ |website=people.com |publisher=People |accessdate=10 April 2020 |date=10 April 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref> all of which were released on 17 April 2020 on [[Netflix]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Masonhall |first1=Erika |title=NETFLIX SPARKS JOY WITH RETURNING UNSCRIPTED FAVORITES RHYTHM + FLOW, THE CIRCLE, AND LOVE IS BLIND, PLUS AN ALL-NEW SHOW FROM MARIE KONDO |url=https://media.netflix.com/en/press-releases/netflix-sparks-joy-with-returning-unscripted-favorites-rhythm-flow-the-circle-and-love-is-blind-plus-an-all-new-show-from-marie-kondo |website=media.netflix.com |publisher=Netflix Media Center |accessdate=28 March 2020 |date=24 March 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n=== Prize ===\nAt the allocation ceremony, the ten remaining contestants became the winners. Bryce Hirschberg, Chloe Veitch, David Birtwistle, Francesca Farago, Harry Jowsey, Kelz Dyke, Lydia Clyma, Nicole O'Brien, Rhonda Paul, and Sharron Townsend all split the {{USD|75000|long=no}} prize fund, resulting in {{USD|7500|long=no}} for each person.<ref>{{Cite episode |title=Lust or Bust |url=https://www.netflix.com/watch/81031053?trackId=200257859 |series=Too Hot to Handle |series-link=Too Hot to Handle (TV series) |network=Netflix |date=17 April 2020 |season=1 |number=8}}</ref>\n\n== Reception ==\nCritic John Serba of ''[[Decider (website)|Decider]]'' panned the show, stating that \"to call it tawdry is to engage in nuclear understatement\", calling it \"some of the dreckiest dreck ever drecked\", and advising viewers to skip it.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Serba |first1=John |title=Stream It Or Skip It: \u2018Too Hot to Handle\u2019 on Netflix, Possibly the Trashiest Reality Show Ever |url=https://decider.com/2020/04/17/too-hot-to-handle-on-netflix-stream-it-or-skip-it/ |website=Decider |accessdate=19 April 2020 |date=17 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nRachelle Hampton of ''[[Slate (magazine)|Slate]]'' also wrote a negative review, stating: \"Despite an irresistibly juicy premise, ''Too Hot to Handle'' doesn\u2019t know what kind of show it wants to be, and it suffers for lack of direction. (...) Its will-they-or-won\u2019t-they concept is ruined as soon as it becomes clear that, yes, they ''obviously'' will, even if it means losing tens of thousands of dollars.\"<ref name=\"Slate\"></ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Netflix original current series}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Too Hot to Handle}}\n[[Category:2020 American television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2020s American reality television series]]\n[[Category:American dating and relationship reality television series]]\n[[Category:English-language television programs]]\n[[Category:Netflix original programming]]\n", "name_user": "Mburati", "label": "safe", "comment": "Link to his biodata", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Too_Hot_to_Handle_(TV_series)"}
{"title_page": "The Daily Wire", "text_new": "{{pp-protected|small=yes}}\n{{short description|American news and opinion website}}\n{{italics}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=January 2020}}\n{{Infobox website\n| name             = ''The Daily Wire''\n| logo             = Dailywirelogo.PNG\n| logo_size        = \n| logo_alt         = \n| logo_caption     = <!-- or:\n| logocaption      = -->\n| screenshot       = \n| collapsible      = <!-- set as \"on\", \"y\", etc, otherwise omit/leave blank -->\n| collapsetext     = <!-- collapsible area's heading (default \"Screenshot\"); omit/leave blank if collapsible not set -->\n| background       = <!-- for collapsetext heading; default grey (gainsboro) -->\n| screenshot_size  = \n| screenshot_alt   = \n| caption          = \n| url              = {{url|https://www.dailywire.com/}}\n| areas            = \n| offices          = \n| commercial       = <!-- \"Yes\", \"No\" or leave blank -->\n| type             = [[online newspaper|news]] and [[opinion journalism|opinion]]\n| registration     = \n| num_users        = \n| content_license  = <!-- or:\n| content_licence  = -->\n| programming_language= \n| owner            = Forward Publishing LLC\n| founders         = \n| author           = {{hlist |[[Ben Shapiro]] |[[Jeremy Boreing]]}}\n| key_people       = {{hlist|Ben Shapiro (editor-in-chief)|Jeremy Boreing ([[Chief operating officer|COO]])|Josh Hammer (editor-at-large)|[[Michael J. Knowles|Michael Knowles]]|[[Andrew Klavan]]|Matt Walsh}}\n| editor           = <!-- or:\n| editors          = -->\n| launch_date      = {{nowrap|{{Start date and years ago|df=no|2015|09|21}}}}\n| revenue          = \n| alexa            = 563 (US, July 2019)<ref name=\"alexa\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.alexa.com/siteinfo/dailywire.com |title=Dailywire.com Site Overview |website=[[Alexa Internet]] |access-date=July 7, 2019}}</ref><!-- {{IncreaseNegative}} {{Steady}} {{DecreasePositive}} [https://www.alexa.com/siteinfo/example.com example.com Traffic Statistics] -->\n| ip               = \n| issn             = <!-- ISSN, e.g. 1085-6706 (automatically linked to https://www.WorldCat.org) -->\n| eissn            = <!-- eISSN, e.g. 1085-6706 (automatically linked to https://www.WorldCat.org) -->\n| oclc             = <!-- OCLC number, useful where an ISSN has not been allocated (automatically linked to https://www.WorldCat.org) -->\n| current_status   = Active\n| footnotes        = \n}}\n\n'''''The Daily Wire''''' is an American [[right-wing]],<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.wbur.org/news/2019/11/14/daily-wire-young-amercians-activists-protesters-bu |title=At Boston University, Conservative Agitator Ben Shapiro Gives Talk Amid Protests, Criticisms |date=November 14, 2019 |website=WBUR News |access-date=November 14, 2019}}</ref> [[Conservatism in the United States|conservative]] news and opinion website founded in 2015 by political commentator [[Ben Shapiro]],<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.politico.com/blogs/on-media/2016/03/michelle-fields-ben-shapiro-resign-from-breitbart-220709 |title=Michelle Fields, Ben Shapiro Resign from Breitbart |last=Gold |first=Hadas |date=March 14, 2016 |work=Politico |access-date=August 15, 2017}}</ref> who is the site's [[editor-in-chief]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.roanoke.com/community/sosalem/political-commentator-ben-shapiro-to-speak-at-roanoke-college-on/article_95429f60-7e99-11e6-a22e-878928626352.html |title=Political commentator Ben Shapiro to Speak at Roanoke College on Thursday |access-date=September 20, 2016 |newspaper=The Roanoke Times}}</ref><ref name=\"MaddausMedia\">{{Cite news |url=https://variety.com/2017/digital/features/breitbart-conservative-media-alt-right-1201963223/ |title=Inside the Battle 'For the Soul of Conservative Media' |last=Maddaus |first=Gene |date=January 19, 2017 |work=Variety |access-date=August 14, 2017}}</ref>\n\n==History==\n''The Daily Wire'' was conceived by Ben Shapiro and [[Jeremy Boreing]], who both worked for ''TruthRevolt'', a news website that was formerly funded by the [[David Horowitz Freedom Center]].<ref name=\"Vanity Fair\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.vanityfair.com/news/2018/12/how-hollywood-invented-ben-shapiro |title='Let's Make You Famous': How Hollywood Invented Ben Shapiro |last=Nguyen, Tina |date=December 9, 2018 |website=Vanity Fair |access-date=December 28, 2018}}</ref> After the duo secured several million dollars in [[Seed money|seed funding]] from [[Dan and Farris Wilks]], ''The Daily Wire'' was launched in 2015, with several former TruthRevolt employees on staff.<ref name=\"Vanity Fair\" /><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://slate.com/news-and-politics/2018/01/is-ben-shapiro-a-conservative-liberals-can-count-on.html |title=The Many Faces of Ben Shapiro |last=Stevenson, Seth |date=January 24, 2018 |website=Slate |access-date=December 28, 2018}}</ref> The website's office is in [[Los Angeles]], [[California]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/10/31/us/california-republicans-bannon-miller-conservative.html |title=In the Heart of 'The Resistance,' California Conservatives Are Invigorated |last=Peters |first=Jeremy W. |date=October 31, 2017 |work=The New York Times |access-date=April 30, 2018  |issn=0362-4331}}</ref>\n\n''The Daily Wire'' became one of the leading news sites and publishers on [[Facebook]] in terms of engagement. In 2018, [[NewsWhip]] identified ''The Daily Wire'' as \"by far\" the top right-wing publisher on Facebook.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://go.newswhip.com/rs/647-QQK-704/images/Hyper-Partisan%20Final.pdf |title=Partisan Publishers and Political Content |date=September 2018 |publisher=NewsWhip |access-date=July 10, 2019}}</ref> According to NewsWhip, ''The Daily Wire'' was the sixth-leading English-language publisher on Facebook in 2019 through the month of March. The site also had the second most articles among Facebook's 10,000 top stories.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://go.newswhip.com/rs/647-QQK-704/images/Facebook%20Publishing%202019_Final.pdf |title=2019 Guide to Publishing on Facebook |date=March 2019 |publisher=NewsWhip |access-date=July 10, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn March 2019, Podtrac ranked ''The Daily Wire''<nowiki/>'s ''[[The Ben Shapiro Show]]'' the second most popular podcast in the U.S., behind ''[[The Daily (podcast)|The Daily]]''.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.insideradio.com/free/a-bounce-for-ben-shapiro-in-march-says-podtrac/article_7fbca710-66d3-11e9-8954-734748203ec0.html |title=A Bounce For Ben Shapiro in March Says Podtrac |date=April 24, 2019 |work=Inside Radio |access-date=June 11, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Podcasts and radio==\nIn addition to its written content, the site produces the following podcasts: ''The Ben Shapiro Show'', ''The Michael Knowles Show'', ''The Matt Walsh Show'', and ''The Andrew Klavan Show''.<ref name=\"DW podcasts\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.dailywire.com/podcasts |title=Podcasts |website=The Daily Wire |access-date=April 25, 2018}}</ref>\n\nThe reach of ''The Ben Shapiro Show'' expanded in April 2018 when [[Westwood One]] began syndicating the podcast to radio.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://politi.co/2pPq43F |title=Ben Shapiro to take his podcast to radio |last=Schwartz |first=Jason |website=Politico |access-date=April 28, 2018}}</ref> In January 2019, Westwood One expanded Shapiro's one-hour podcast-to-radio program, adding a nationally syndicated two-hour live radio show, for three hours of Ben Shapiro programming daily.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.insideradio.com/free/ben-shapiro-radio-show-expands-to-three-hours-over-the/article_f8a5d07a-c020-11e8-b7ae-a3f6cb9d9b7b.html |title=Ben Shapiro Radio Show Expands To Three Hours Over The Air |date=September 24, 2018 |work=Inside Radio |access-date=June 16, 2019}}</ref> {{as of|2019|March}}, according to Westwood One, ''The Ben Shapiro Show'' is being carried by more than 200 stations, including in nine of the top ten markets.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.westwoodone.com/2019/03/06/the-ben-shapiro-show-experiences-explosive-station-growth-and-ratings-success-by-drawing-younger-listeners-to-broadcast-radio/ |title=The Ben Shapiro Show Experiences Explosive Station Growth and Ratings Success by Drawing Younger Listeners to Broadcast Radio |date=March 6, 2019 |publisher=Westwood One}}</ref>\n\n==Controversies==\nAccording to [[Snopes]], \"DailyWire.com has a tendency to share stories that are taken out of context or not verified\", including reports on protesters digging up Confederate graves, Democratic congresspeople refusing to stand for a fallen [[United States Navy SEALs|Navy SEAL]]'s widow, and [[Harvard University]] holding segregated [[Graduation|commencement ceremonies]].<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.snopes.com/fact-check/is-mohammed-popular-name-netherlands/ |title=FACT CHECK: Is Mohammed the Most Popular Name for Newborn Boys in the Netherlands? |work=Snopes.com |access-date=April 29, 2018 }}</ref> \n\nAccording to [[FactCheck.org]], ''The Daily Wire'' incorrectly credited HUD Secretary [[Ben Carson]] with finding over $500&nbsp;billion in accounting errors made by the Obama administration when the errors were discovered and published by HUD's independent inspector general before Carson became secretary.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.factcheck.org/2017/04/carson-didnt-find-hud-errors/ |title=Carson Didn't Find HUD Errors |date=April 19, 2017 |work=FactCheck.org |access-date=April 29, 2018 }}</ref>\n\n''The Daily Wire'' has published articles expressing skepticism that [[Global warming|climate change]] is occurring and that [[Scientific consensus on climate change|humans contribute to climate change]]. Climate scientists have described the articles as inaccurate and misleading.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://climatefeedback.org/evaluation/daily-wire-article-misunderstands-study-carbon-budget-along-fox-news-telegraph-daily-mail-breitbart-james-barrett/ |title=Daily Wire article misunderstands study on carbon budget (along with Fox News, The Telegraph, The Daily Mail, Breitbart\u2026) |date=September 21, 2017 |work=Climate Feedback |access-date=April 29, 2018 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://climatefeedback.org/evaluation/global-quackery-earth-not-warmed-past-19-years-new-study-finds-joseph-curl-the-daily-wire/ |title=The Daily Wire makes wild claims about climate change based on no evidence |date=May 9, 2017 |work=Climate Feedback |access-date=April 29, 2018 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://climatefeedback.org/evaluation/scientists-we-know-what-really-causes-climate-james-barrett-the-daily-wire/ |title=Analysis of 'Scientists: Here's What Really Causes Climate Change (And It Has Nothing To Do With Human Beings)' |date=February 28, 2017 |work=Climate Feedback |access-date=April 29, 2018 }}</ref>\n\nThe investigative website [[Judd Legum|Popular Information]] accused ''The Daily Wire'' in October 2019 of violating Facebook's policies by creating 14 anonymous pages promoting its content exclusively to boost engagement. A new Facebook policy might force them to add their ownership to their pages.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2019/nov/07/facebook-we-would-let-tories-run-doctored-starmer-video-as-ad |title=Facebook: we would let Tories run 'doctored' Starmer video as ad |last=Hern |first=Alex |date=November 7, 2019 |work=The Guardian |access-date=November 11, 2019 |last2=Waterson |first2=Jim}}</ref> Facebook told Popular Information that it would take no action against ''The Daily Wire''.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://popular.info/p/facebook-allows-prominent-right-wing |title=Facebook allows prominent right-wing website to break the rules |last=Information |first=Judd at Popular |website=popular.info |access-date=November 9, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[Blaze Media]]\n* [[Breitbart News]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{official website}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Daily Wire, The}}\n[[Category:American conservative websites]]\n[[Category:Internet properties established in 2015]]\n[[Ca