  = [[FIBA Americas]] ([[Americas]])\n| folded      = \n| champion    = [[Leones de Santo Domingo]]<br/>(2nd title)\n| most_champs = [[Metros de Santiago]] (5 titles)\n| TV          = \n| website     = [http://www.lnb.com.do lnb.com.do]\n}}\nThe '''Liga Nacional de Baloncesto''' ('''LNB''') is the top men's professional [[basketball]] league in the [[Dominican Republic]]. Established in 2005, eight teams compete annually in a Summer season.\n\n==Teams==\n===North===\n* [[Huracanes del Atl\u00e1ntico]]\n* [[Indios de San Francisco de Macor\u00eds]]\n* [[Metros de Santiago]]\n* [[Reales de La Vega]]\n\n===South===\n* [[Ca\u00f1eros del Este]]\n* [[Soles de Santo Domingo Este]]\n* [[Leones de Santo Domingo]]\n* [[Titanes del Distrito Nacional]]\n\n==Champions==\n{| align=center width=70% border=1 cellpadding=\"2\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"background: #f9f9f9; border: 1px #aaa solid; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 95%; text-align: center;\"\n|- align=center bgcolor=#0000CC style=\"color:white;\"\n!'''Season'''\n!Champion\n!Runner-up\n!Series\n|-\n|2005 ||'''[[Reales de La Vega]]'''\n|[[Panteras del Distrito Nacional]]\n|4\u20131 (best-of 7)\n|-\n|2006 ||'''[[Metros de Santiago]]'''\n|[[Constituyentes de San Crist\u00f3bal]]\n|4\u20133 (best-of 7)\n|-\n|2007 ||'''[[Metros de Santiago]]'''\n|[[Panteras del Distrito Nacional]]\n|4\u20132 (best-of 7)\n|-\n|2008 ||'''[[Constituyentes de San Crist\u00f3bal]]'''\n|[[Reales de La Vega]]\n|4\u20132 (best-of 7)\n|-\n|2009 ||colspan=3|''No league held''\n|-\n|2010 ||'''[[Ca\u00f1eros del Este]]'''\n|[[Tiburones de Puerto Plata]]\n|4\u20131 (best-of 7)\n|-\n|2011 ||'''[[Leones de Santo Domingo]]'''\n|[[Cocolos de San Pedro de Macor\u00eds]]\n|4\u20132 (best-of 7)\n|-\n|2012 ||'''[[Ca\u00f1eros del Este]]'''\n|[[Indios de San Francisco de Macor\u00eds]]\n|4\u20132 (best-of 7)\n|-\n|2013 ||'''[[Indios de San Francisco de Macor\u00eds]]'''<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://mundodelosperiodista.blogspot.com/2013/09/indios-nuevos-campeones-de-la-lnb-2013.html|title = Indios nuevos campeones de la LNB 2013|date = September 2013|accessdate = |website = El Mundo de los Periodistas|publisher = |last = |first = }}</ref>\n|[[Titanes del Licey]]\n|4\u20133 (best-of 7)\n|-\n|2014 ||'''[[Metros de Santiago]]'''<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://figureocity.com/deportes/metros-de-santiago-se-proclaman-campeones-de-la-lnb-2014/|title = Metros de Santiago se proclaman campeones de la LNB 2014|date = 12 July 2014|accessdate = |website = Figureocity.com|publisher = |last = |first = }}</ref>\n|[[Titanes del Distrito Nacional]]\n|4\u20132 (best-of 7)\n|-\n|2015 ||'''[[Metros de Santiago]]'''\n|[[Ca\u00f1eros del Este]]\n|4\u20133 (best-of 7)\n|-\n|2016 ||'''[[Leones de Santo Domingo]]'''\n|[[Metros de Santiago]]\n|4\u20133 (best-of 7)\n|-\n|2017 ||'''[[Metros de Santiago]]'''\n|[[Leones de Santo Domingo]]\n|4\u20131 (best-of 7)\n|-\n|2018 ||'''[[Reales de La Vega]]'''\n|[[Ca\u00f1eros del Este]]\n|4\u20132 (best-of 7)\n|}\n\n== Awards ==\n=== Most Valuable Player ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!Year\n!Winner\n!Team\n!{{tooltip|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n|2005\t\n|{{flagicon|USA}} {{sortname|Ed|Elisma}}\n|[[Marineros de Puerto Plata]]\n|<ref>{{Cite news|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20051029153021/http://www.ldb.com.do/noticias06092005.php|url=http://www.ldb.com.do/noticias06092005.php|title=Eddie Elisma Jugador M\u00e1s Valioso de Lidoba|language=es|website=ldb.com.do|date=September 6, 2005|archive-date=October 29, 2005|access-date=April 20, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|2006\n|{{flagicon|DOM}} {{sortname|Alexis|Montas}}\n|[[Ca\u00f1eros de La Romana]]\n|\n|-\n|2007\n|{{flagicon|DOM}} {{sortname|Juan|Araujo|dab=basketball}}\n|[[Panteras del Distrito Nacional]]\n|<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://listindiario.com/el-deporte/2007/10/05/31588/la-lidoba-anuncia-el-equipo-todos-estrellas|title=La Lidoba anuncia el equipo Todos Estrellas|language=es|newspaper=[[List\u00edn Diario]]|date=October 5, 2007|access-date=April 20, 20